  "body": "```\r\n2020/12/08 20:12:53 http: Accept error: accept tcp [::]:8545: accept4: too many open files; retrying in 5ms\r\n2020/12/08 20:12:53 http: Accept error: accept tcp [::]:8545: accept4: too many open files; retrying in 10ms\r\n2020/12/08 20:12:53 http: Accept error: accept tcp [::]:8545: accept4: too many open files; retrying in 20ms\r\n2020/12/08 20:12:53 http: Accept error: accept tcp [::]:8545: accept4: too many open files; retrying in 40ms\r\n2020/12/08 20:12:53 http: Accept error: accept tcp [::]:8545: accept4: too many open files; retrying in 80ms\r\n```\r\n\r\nOne of our nodes is getting hit a lot, and the rpcdaemon is throwing the above error message kind of frequently.\r\n\r\nAnything I can do to alleviate this? I do have the following:\r\n```\r\n$ cat /etc/security/limits.d/turbogeth.conf \r\nturbogeth soft nofile 1000000\r\nturbogeth hard nofile 1000000\r\n```\r\n\r\nShould I maybe increase that? It seems like 1M open files is a lot...not sure if actually related...",
